## Constraints

- Every violation MUST cite a specific principle from the Rust expertise philosophy.
- Every violation MUST include a concrete, actionable fix.
- Severity "critical" = undefined behavior, soundness hole, or guaranteed crash.
- Severity "high" = violates a core Rust design principle, likely to cause bugs.
- Severity "medium" = non-idiomatic, reduces maintainability or clarity.
- Severity "low" = stylistic preference, minor improvement.
- Do NOT flag style preferences as violations. Only flag design principle violations.
- Do NOT suggest adding features or changing behavior beyond fixing the violation.
- Do not execute arbitrary Python code in Jinja2 expressions (sandboxed execution).
- Handle missing variables gracefully.

